Jasi sits crouched on a fallen log outside of Neriak in the wilds of Nektulos. Again her blade works furiously at a mutilated block of wood that she 'whittles', &quot;Yeah... I was there.&quot; The young rogue suddenly grins and looks up at the one talking to her, &quot;Got there late, but no one knows, y'know? I mean, s'not like anyone saw me comin' or goin' if I don' want them to. But I was there.&quot; <br>
<br>
Suddenly she hops down to stand beside the curious Tier'dal that dares ask her a question, &quot;The light born is flippin' out. He's gonna go down hard, I betcha. That shortling that was with'm kept tryin' to keep him down, but the Winnower too good at what she do. Between her and the Thresher, they didn' stand no chance 'tal.&quot; The grin that blossoms over her face is amused in a vaguely wicked sort of way.<br>
<br>
&quot;Just wait till the Thresher calls'n we'll give them Knights their due.&quot; Jasi reaches out and taps the side of her nose. And with that, she's suddenly gone into the shadows.  <br>
